properties.Title: Storm Surge Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Warning of potential breaking sea conditions and overwash issued jointly by Fisheries and Oceans Canada (Science) and the Meteorological Service of Canada - Quebec Area on 2020-11-23. Higher than normal water levels and large waves are expected near the coast in the concerned areas. An intense low pressure system approaching from New England will give strong winds over the areas listed below. The combination of these winds and the current run of medium-amplitude tidal ranges may produce minor breaking sea conditions along the coast near the following localities, on the dates and at the times specified (Eastern Standard Time). Forillon Park - Gaspé - Percé: 2020-11-23, from 7:30 P.M. to 10:30 P.M. New-Carlisle - Chandler: 2020-11-23, from 07:30 PM to 10:30 PM. Anticosti: 2020-11-23, from 07:30 PM to 10:30 PM. Natashquan: 2020-11-23, from 04:00 PM to 07:30 PM. ### Storm surge warnings are issued when water levels pose a threat to coastal regions. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Storm Surge Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Higher than normal water levels with large waves are expected near the coast. Warning of potential breaking sea conditions and overwash issued jointly by Fisheries and Oceans Canada (Science) and the Meteorological Service of Canada - Quebec Area on 2020-11-23. Higher than normal water levels and large waves are expected near the coast in the concerned areas. An intense low pressure system approaching from New England will give high winds over the areas listed below. The combination of these winds and the current run of medium-amplitude tidal ranges may produce minor breaking sea conditions along the coast near the following localities, on the dates and at the times specified (Eastern Standard Time). Rimouski - Mont-Joli: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Matane: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Sainte-Anne-des-Monts - Grande-Vallée: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Forillon Park - Gaspé - Percé: 2020-11-24, from 08:00 AM to 12:00 PM. Anticosti: 2020-11-24, from 07:30 AM to 11:30 AM. Natashquan: 2020-11-24, from 04:30 AM to 08:30 AM. Chevery: 2020-11-24, from 04:00 AM to 08:00 AM. Blanc-Sablon: 2020-11-24, from 04:00 AM to 08:00 AM. ### Storm surge warnings are issued when water levels pose a threat to coastal regions. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Winter Storm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Hazardous winter conditions are expected. Time span: this evening until overnight Tuesday night. Total snowfall: 30 to 45 cm. Maximum wind gusts: northwesterly 90 km/h Tuesday evening. Locations: Rigolet and vicinity. Remarks: Snow will become heavy, at times, this evening, and continue through the day Tuesday, before gradually easing Tuesday night. Strong north to northwesterly winds will accompany the snow Tuesday afternoon and evening causing reduced visibility in blowing snow. Conditions are expected to improve by morning on Wednesday. ### Visibility will be suddenly reduced to near zero at times in heavy snow and blowing snow. Winter storm warnings are issued when multiple types of severe winter weather are expected to occur together. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong winds that may cause damage are expected or occurring. Maximum gusts: west or southwesterly 80 km/h, except 100 km/h along parts of the coast. Locations: northern Newfoundland. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with gusty winds and visibility frequently near zero in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. A deep low pressure system over the Gulf of Alaska will combine with an Arctic ridge over the Northwest Territories to give rise to strong east winds of 70 km/h gusting to 90 near the Richardson Mountains. These strong winds will cause poor visibility in blowing snow and wind chill values near minus 25. Blizzard conditions will begin early this evening and then end overnight. ### Travel is expected to be extremely hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #YTStorm.
